The issue of poor or no access to water remains a day-to-day challenge for many communities around KwaZulu Natal. eNCA reporter Lethiwe Mdluli has been on the scene. Courtesy of #DStv403 DURBAN - Twenty water tanks will be provided to the Hambanathi community in KwaZulu-Natal following a water protest there. Angry residents took to the streets and blocked roads over lack of water for close to three months. READ: SAHRC looking into KZN water crisis The community accused the municipality of not providing enough water tankers to the township, leaving residents helpless. * eNCA’s Lethiwe Mdluli reports.